rms how economists and data scientists at corporations, regulatory agencies, and insurance companies develop and use these price tags and points a spotlight at their logical flaws and limitations. He then forcefully argues against the rampant unfairness in the system. Readers will be enlightened, shocked, and, ultimately, empowered to confront the price tags we assign to human lives and understand why such calculations matter.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aEquality. 0aSocial valuesxPolitical aspects. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / General.2bisacsh  aabortion.  acompensation.  acorporate dumping.  acorporations.  acriminal justice.  adeath.  aeconomics.  aeconomy.  aethics.  ahealth insurance.  ahealth.  ahealthcare.  ahuman life.  ainequality.  ainsurance.  alaws.  alawsuits.  alegal settlements.  alegal system.  amorality.  anonfiction.  aparenting.  aphilosophy.  apolitical science.  apolitics.  apoverty.  aprecarity.  apublic policy.  arace.  areproductive rights.  asafe water.  ascience.  asocial issues.  asocial justice.  asocial policy.  atoxic waste.  aundervalued lives.  avalue.  awealth inequality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2020 Englishz978311070479208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2020z9783110704624oZDB-23-DBV08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520974685zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter